Diagnosis.
Dorsally green, ventrally greenish yellow (
Fig. 5G,H
). Antennae black with base of segment IV and basal third of V whitish (
Fig. 5G
); first segment mostly green with dorsal surface smoky black (
Fig. 5G
). Anterolateral margins of pronotum greenish yellow, each with a green parallel line. Costal margins of coria each with a black stripe which occupies 1/5 of its extension. Each corium with a large brown spot on anterior 2/3 between claval suture and costal vein (
Fig. 5G
). Punctures of coria black. Abdomen with intersegmental areas and pseudosutures slightly darker than remaining surfaces (
Fig. 5H
). Pygophore with posterolateral angles slightly projected, rounded, tumid (
Fig. 4A
). Superior process of genital cup strongly developed (
Fig. 4B
). Mesial borders of gonocoxites 8 divergent distally leaving visible part of gonapophyses 8 (
Fig. 4D
). Gonocoxites 9 slightly compressed laterally as compared with other species in this group (
Fig. 4D
).

Thorax. Humeral angles each with a black spot on apex (
Fig. 5G,H
). Scutellum with apex impunctate. Veins of coria greenish yellow (
Fig. 5G
). Membranes of hemelytra light brown (
Fig. 5G
). Ventral surface with shallow, black punctation (
Fig. 5H
).

Abdomen. Distal third of seventh abdominal segments black (
Fig. 5G
).

Female (
Fig. 4D
). Gonocoxites 8 slightly concave, outer lateral margins straight, distally projected, but not reaching middle of laterotergites 9. Gonocoxites 9 each with medial keel restricted to basal half. Laterotergites 9 shallowly concave basally; apices clearly surpassing sclerite uniting laterotergites 8.
